content.description:
Sit start left on the jugs, come around to top out on the face.

Not a FA considering there’s a good amount of chalk but a fun little climb!
content.location: Immediately to the left of Chips

content.description: Sit start matched on the block-like feature, make 3 moves up on opposing side pulls then bump right hand to a crimp. Move left hand to a crimp then climb up and left on edges topping out with a mantel at the apex of the overhang.
content.location: Located on the other side of the boulder from planet of the apes

content.description: Sit start on Bubbatronic (large jugs on shield) and connect into the finish on Planet of the Apes.  Great moves slightly harder than original
An eliminate, avoid the right rail on Planet and climb up the cool incut flakes making a big move to the center sloper ontop.
content.location: The route straight up from the double-kneebar, between Chips and Planet.

content.description: Begin in a large undercling jug to the right.  Climb up a series of slopey sidepulls for the right hand, and crimps for the left.  Top out is still hard.

Sit start on the bottom left of the arete with hands on the large pocket and feet on the rail underneath. Any and all feet in the underside are on. Follow pockets/jugs along and above the arete to the right. Top on on the jug near the end of the arete that is almost at the top. The rail above the pockets midway through the problem is off.
content.protection: Two crash pads should be good.
content.location: On the backside (uphill) of the Chip and Dale boulder along the arete. Across the boulder from the Chips route.

content.description: Not sure why there hasn’t been a sit start added to the classic “Chips” but it looked fun. This climb starts on the juggy start to “planet of the grapes”. Go right hand up then left into the undercling. Get the knee bar and bring your right hand over. Then finish through “Chips”.
content.location: Same sit start as planet of the grapes.

content.description: This problem begins on Planet of the Apes but instead of getting the crimp with your left hand go to it with your right. Work your way left around the corner and get the rail feature with your left hand. The higher the better because the next move is a deadpoint dyno up and right although I have seen people do it static using an intermediate hold.  Some people think this is easier than Planet of the Apes.
Sit start low on jugs and head up through some  slopey crimps and pinches with big feet and a accuracy shot into a finger slot at the top. Easy mantle
content.location: Bubbatronic is locate to the right of Planet of the Apes

content.description: Sit start on a slopey rail one foot off the ground. Gaston and crimp your way up to better holds for the topout.
